Firbi or Celte this is the question =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raeloran@lighttanksofdaoc>Raeloran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#000000>(11/18/02 3:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bluntmaster</span><hr size=1> Firbolgs have higher starting strength and lower dexterity and quickness than celts. That means firbies will on average hit harder and evade and parry less than celts. However, I don't think it really makes that big of a difference in the long run. One thing to remember is that firbies are bigger and will stand out in a group. That means you will be targeted easier. One one hand, being targetted easier means you will get hit more often. But that hit you take is one less that the healers and mages have to take. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 42 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deadlysinx>DeadlysinX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(11/19/02 1:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> No more advice ? =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.s